// C2: Acting Components
instance CartMovementMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Dedicated motor for horizontal cart movement along the gantry crane's bridge, controlled via embedded controller with trajectory validation for safety."
]

instance HoistingMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Motor for vertical hoisting movement, integrated with electromagnet for container manipulation, constrained by physical limits of the crane structure."
]

instance CraneElectromagnet : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Electromagnet at the end of the hoist for manipulating small pucks representing containers, interfaced with embedded controllers for remote actuation."
]

// C3: Physical Sensing Components
instance SwingAngleEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Measures swinging motion of the hoist to ensure trajectory accuracy in the gantry crane system."
    DTDFVocab:producedData SwingAngleDataTransmitted
]

instance CraneAnemometer : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Quantifies wind speed affecting the crane's hoist and payload movement for precise trajectory control."
    DTDFVocab:producedData WindSpeedDataTransmitted
]

instance AirQualitySensorSet : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Set of sensors (unspecified types) deployed on Raspberry Pi for measuring indoor air quality parameters like CO2 and particulate matter."
    DTDFVocab:producedData AirQualityDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-Virtual Interaction
instance SwingAngleDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom SwingAngleEncoder
]

instance WindSpeedDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom CraneAnemometer
]

instance AirQualityDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom AirQualitySensorSet
]

instance CraneStateDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom PhysicalCraneInterface
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance KinematicModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "CAD-based kinematic model of the gantry crane created using Autodesk Fusion 360, representing joint angles, velocities, and accelerations for simulation."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo Fusion360Enabler
]

instance BehavioralAdaptationModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Behavioral adaptation model for real-time control algorithms optimizing crane operations like trajectory planning and energy efficiency."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo GantryLibEnabler
]

instance AutomationMLModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "AutomationML-based model for air quality management digital twin, enabling structured data exchange and simulation pipelines."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo AutomationMLEngineEnabler
]

instance PreRecordedGreenhouseData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Embedded time-series data in virtual machine images for initialization and simulation of greenhouse digital twin systems."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo InfluxDBEnabler
]

instance CraneOperationalData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Time-series operational data including kinematic states (joint angles, velocities, accelerations), trajectory execution metrics, and controller signals."
    DTDFVocab:fromData CraneStateDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo TimescaleDBEnabler
]

instance AirQualityHistoricalData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Historical time-series data of indoor air quality parameters (CO2, particulate matter) for longitudinal analysis and predictive analytics."
    DTDFVocab:fromData AirQualityDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo InfluxDBEnabler
]

// C11: Enablers
instance Fusion360Enabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Autodesk Fusion 360 for creating and managing the crane's kinematic CAD model and geometric representations."
]

instance GantryLibEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Custom Python module (gantrylib) for data processing, control logic, and digital twin services integration."
    DTDFVocab:enables OptimalControlService, ContinuousValidationService, DataVisualizationService
]

instance DockerEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Containerization framework ensuring reproducibility and portability of the digital twin environment across deployments."
    DTDFVocab:enables DeploymentService
]

instance TimescaleDBEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Time-series database storing historical operational data with SQL-like querying capabilities for crane metrics."
    DTDFVocab:enables HistoricalDataLoggingService, ContinuousValidationService
]

instance GrafanaEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Real-time dashboard hosting platform for monitoring crane metrics like position, velocity, and system health."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataVisualizationService
]

instance MosquittoMQTTEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Eclipse Mosquitto MQTT broker facilitating bidirectional, low-latency data streaming between physical crane and digital twin."
    DTDFVocab:enables PhysicalVirtualInteractionService
]

instance AzureCloudEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Microsoft Azure tools enabling cloud-based model execution, data processing, and predictive analytics for air quality management."
    DTDFVocab:enables SimulationPredictionService
]

instance AutomationMLEngineEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "AutomationML engine for model-driven engineering, enabling standardized data exchange and simulation pipelines."
    DTDFVocab:enables AirQualitySimulationService
]

instance InfluxDBEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Time-series database for storing pre-recorded greenhouse data and air quality metrics with efficient querying capabilities."
    DTDFVocab:enables GreenhouseDataLoggingService
]

// C6: Services
instance OptimalControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Implements real-time control algorithms for trajectory planning and energy efficiency optimization in crane operations."
    DTDFVocab:provides CraneTrajectoryOptimizationAction, EnergyEfficiencyInsight
]

instance HistoricalDataLoggingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Stores time-series operational data for post-processing and longitudinal analysis of crane behavior."
    DTDFVocab:provides CraneBehaviorAnalysisInsight
]

instance DataVisualizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Delivers Grafana dashboard for real-time monitoring of crane metrics and Python-based front-end for interactive data exploration."
    DTDFVocab:provides CraneMetricsDashboardInsight
]

instance ContinuousValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Employs distance metrics and threshold-based validation to compare physical and digital system states for real-time synchronization and anomaly detection."
    DTDFVocab:provides SystemStateValidationInsight, FaultDetectionAction
]

instance PhysicalVirtualInteractionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Facilitates continuous data exchange between physical crane and digital twin via MQTT broker for low-latency updates."
    DTDFVocab:provides RealTimeDataSynchronizationInsight
]

instance SimulationPredictionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Leverages Azure tools for predictive analytics including virus spread risk assessment in construction environments."
    DTDFVocab:provides AirQualityPredictionInsight
]

instance AirQualitySimulationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "AutomationML-based simulation pipeline for structured data exchange and air quality modeling."
    DTDFVocab:provides AirQualityScenarioAnalysisInsight
]

instance DeploymentService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Ensures reproducible deployment of digital twin environment using containerization."
    DTDFVocab:provides SystemReproducibilityInsight
]

instance GreenhouseDataLoggingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Stores pre-recorded greenhouse time-series data in InfluxDB for initialization and simulation."
    DTDFVocab:provides GreenhouseEnvironmentInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance CraneTrajectoryOptimizationAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automatically adjusts crane trajectories for optimal performance based on real-time kinematic data."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance EnergyEfficiencyInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Provides operational insights for energy-efficient crane movements through behavioral adaptation models."
]

instance CraneBehaviorAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Enables longitudinal analysis of crane kinematic states and operational patterns for performance evaluation."
]

instance CraneMetricsDashboardInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time visualization of crane position, velocity, and system health metrics via Grafana dashboard."
]

instance SystemStateValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Continuous comparison of physical and digital twin states using distance metrics for validation."
]

instance FaultDetectionAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Detects anomalies in crane operation through threshold-based validation of physical-digital state discrepancies."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance RealTimeDataSynchronizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Ensures low-latency, event-driven synchronization between physical crane and digital twin via MQTT."
]

instance AirQualityPredictionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Predictive analytics for indoor air quality including virus spread risk assessment in construction environments."
]

instance AirQualityScenarioAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Structured simulation of air quality scenarios using AutomationML-based models for operational planning."
]

instance SystemReproducibilityInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Ensures consistent deployment of digital twin across environments through containerization."
]

instance GreenhouseEnvironmentInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Provides environmental control insights for greenhouse systems using pre-recorded data initialization."
]

// C1: Physical System Environment
instance LabScaleGantryCraneEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Closed-loop, deterministic laboratory environment for testing digital twin models of a scaled-down mechanical gantry crane."
    base:contains PhysicalCraneComponent, EmbeddedControllerComponent, SensorNetworkComponent
]

instance PhysicalCraneComponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Mechanical gantry crane with movable components (bridge, trolley, payload hook) for material handling in controlled environments."
]

instance EmbeddedControllerComponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Dedicated control system interfacing with crane actuators (motors, encoders) to execute commands with trajectory validation."
]

instance SensorNetworkComponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Localized sensor network including swing angle encoder, anemometer, and embedded controllers for real-time data acquisition."
]

instance RaspberryPiComponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Single-board computer for sensor data acquisition and edge computing in air quality management systems."
]

// C4: Additional Data Transmission (PhysicalCraneInterface)
instance PhysicalCraneInterface : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Python program connecting to crane controllers to capture real-time state data (position, puck movement, controller signals)."
    DTDFVocab:producedData CraneStateDataTransmitted
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Control flows from the digital twin to the physical gantry crane are executed via the **Control Application**, a Python-based system that interfaces with the **Physical Crane Interface**. Commands include trajectory generation (e.g., optimal movement paths without residual swinging) and operational directives (e.g., puck placement). The **Trajectory Generator Service** produces kinematically optimized trajectories, which are validated by the **Simulation Service** before execution. Control messages are transmitted via the **MQTT Broker**, with formats unspecified but assumed to align with the crane's controller protocols. Validation and authentication mechanisms are not explicitly described, though the **Continuous Validation Service** implies real-time comparison of executed trajectories against simulations to detect deviations. Feedback systems include operator notifications via the **Dashboard** (Grafana) when thresholds are breached. Conflict resolution and command execution confirmation are not detailed, but the system’s design suggests a closed-loop architecture where deviations trigger alerts."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system exhibits asynchronous temporal synchronization in the GreenhouseDT exemplar, where virtual machine images are preloaded with prerecorded data, suggesting offline or batch-based validation rather than real-time updates. The Air Quality Management exemplar supports three distinct temporal applications: **runtime visualization** (real-time or near-real-time monitoring), **simulation** (time-accelerated or deterministic modeling), and **prediction** (forward-looking forecasting with unspecified granularity). The Gantry Crane system implies continuous validation and real-time status updates, though no explicit synchronization frequency or latency requirements are documented. No explicit mention of temporal granularity (e.g., millisecond, second, minute) or service-specific time scales (e.g., sensor polling rates) is provided in the documents."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin systems in the documents adopt a **lightweight, ad-hoc orchestration approach** rather than relying on commercial frameworks. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplifies a **self-adaptive digital twin** with **behavioral adaptation** for both the physical greenhouse and its digital counterpart, coordinated via **InfluxDB (time-series database)** and **ActiveMQ (message broker)**. The **Air Quality Management** exemplar uses **Microsoft Azure tools** for pipeline implementation, integrating **AutomationML** for model-driven engineering and **Raspberry Pi-based sensors** for real-time data ingestion. Both exemplars emphasize **containerization/virtualization** (e.g., virtual machine images, Docker-like dissemination) to ensure **modularity and reproducibility**. The **gantry crane** system, though not detailed in orchestration, aligns with this pattern by leveraging **C4 Model architecture** for **context and container-level coordination**, suggesting a **cyber-physical system (CPS)-centric constellation** with **loosely coupled components**. No explicit **resource management policies** (e.g., QoS, priority scheduling) or **federated twin architectures** are described."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "
The **lab-scale gantry crane** employs a **Continuous Validation Service** that **continuously compares measurements of executed trajectories** (e.g., motor positions, swing angles) with simulations. This service calculates **distance metrics** between real and simulated trajectories and compares the result against an **acceptable threshold** to detect deviations. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar implies **dynamic fidelity adjustments** via self-adaptive behavioral models, while the **Air Quality Management** system likely supports **cloud-based validation** through Microsoft Azure tools. Quality assurance processes for the gantry crane are architecture-driven, leveraging the **C4 Model** for consistency checks, though explicit uncertainty quantification or error correction mechanisms are not detailed.
"
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The digital twin’s technical network infrastructure relies on a **service-oriented architecture** with the **MQTT Broker** as the central communication hub for inter-service signaling. The **TimescaleDB database** stores all system-generated data, while the **Dashboard (Grafana)** visualizes real-time metrics. Network topology is not explicitly defined, but the use of MQTT suggests a lightweight, publish-subscribe model suitable for edge deployments. Bandwidth and latency requirements are not quantified, though continuous validation implies low-latency constraints for trajectory comparison. Reliability and redundancy mechanisms are not described, but the system’s ability to operate without the digital twin hints at offline-capable components. Security protocols are unspecified, though the use of a dedicated broker and centralized database may imply basic access controls."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The digital twin system is deployed entirely on a **personal computer**, with all six containers (e.g., **TimescaleDB**, **Grafana Dashboard**, **Trajectory Generator Service**) running locally. Computational requirements are inferred to support real-time trajectory generation, simulation, and validation, though specific CPU/GPU or memory constraints are not provided. Storage demands are met by **TimescaleDB**, optimized for time-series data. Scalability mechanisms are not addressed, as the system is tailored for a lab-scale gantry crane with no mention of distributed deployment. Availability and reliability are assured by the crane's ability to operate autonomously without the digital twin, though no explicit failover or backup strategies are documented."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system demonstrates **limited, domain-specific horizontal integration**. The GreenhouseDT exemplar integrates with **InfluxDB** (time-series database) and **ActiveMQ** (message broker) for internal data exchange, with no external system dependencies documented. The Air Quality Management exemplar relies on **AutomationML** (a standardized engineering data format) for Digital Twin modeling and **Microsoft Azure tools** for cloud-based pipeline execution, implying interoperability with **construction engineering tools** (e.g., CAD/BIM software) but without explicit protocol details. The Gantry Crane system lacks documented external integrations, though the broader context suggests potential alignment with **logistics or cyber-physical systems (CPS) frameworks**. No ERP, IoT platform, or cross-Digital Twin federation protocols (e.g., OPC UA, MQTT) are mentioned."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The only explicitly mentioned **standardization effort** is the use of **AutomationML** in the Air Quality Management exemplar for digital twin modeling. No other industry standards (e.g., IEC 62714, ASHRAE 62.1, ISO 16890, or FAO standards), certification frameworks, or interoperability protocols (e.g., OPC UA, MQTT) are referenced in the provided documents. The ad-hoc nature of the implementations precludes adherence to formal compliance frameworks."
]